author: Cheryl Wray | cwray@al.com
title: Joey Logano wins under caution at Talladega; Dale Jr. out of Chase race
text:
Comments 
Joey Logano won under caution today in the CampingWorld.com 500 at Talladega. 
Logano came into the race in first place in the Sprint Cup Series Chase standings. The race was the last of the Contender Round and reduced the 12 still in the Chase down to eight. 
Fan favorite Dale Earnhardt Jr. was eliminated from the Chase, despite leading a race-high 61 laps Sunday and finishing second; he had to win at Talladega to keep in the championship hunt.
